A friend of mine recently moved from Western Europe to Russia and said the biggest shock was how there are still normal people there. Not in the sense of "normies", but like legitimately normal people that are just not mentally ill at all, the baseline sanity of people is higher.

He said moving to Russia he realized the ambiance of neurosis pervasive everywhere in the West today that he was used to living with was suddenly just gone there. People in Russia are simply not "performative" like everyone in the West now, no one is "therapized". Normal people.

Galkovsky made an interesting point that billionaires don't really exist. What people imagine when they hear a billionaire in reality is a person with ~30 million dollars. But billionaires are either fused with the state or  representatives of the mafia, organized crime, politics

I know we're Eastern Europeans here so everyone is colder and unfriendlier but there's no way this is normal. I can understand people posting a family photo from a vacation together but this is just bizarre. I don't know I would have to leave the country out of shame or something

I obviously don't want to put any blame on his poor family, but isn't this sorta psychotic to people? Like I genuinely cannot imagine my mother posting pictures of me like this in any possible universe. This is posted in public for hundreds of people to see, how is it not insane?

There's this sort of subconscious urge of some mothers to baby and embarrass their sons (that is a natural albeit undesirable part of the family dynamic), but this is legitimately dishonoring, I don't know how you wouldn't join the Merchant Marine and disappear to escape from it.

Mormons (I thought) seem more traditional like old school societies where everyone outside of the family is looked at with some suspicion and hostility so you would never post anything even slightly embarrassing for them to see, this feels like wholesome chungus Evangelical stuff
If you're some really handsome Gigachad type pulling women from a young age it would obviously be no issue but if you're an awkward self-conscious guy insecure about his looks it must be like torture
